race.comment: The speedy SKY LAND (3) went back-to-back at Hobart and has been around the mark her two since. She will hit the ground running from the inside barrier and is thrown in with the 4kg claim. She'll be tough to peg back. THE LAST HURRAH (1) Is another leader who followed a comfortable CL2 win at Hobart with a close-up effort at the track in stronger than this. Has the speed to clear the awkward gate and presents freshened. The 2kg claim brings her into it. RED SPHERE (2) is an improver coming back to the turf. He can get into the finish with average luck in the run. BAYBOUGG (6) has been freshened and is better than the form line suggests. She's trialled well at Devonport and has to be kept onside.
